<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,258,858]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,434,366,391]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44">Species description.</emphasis>
Prosome ovoid in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[803,875,366,390]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,249,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[197,1389,905,1964]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[192,1395,903,1969]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Pertsovius serratus gen. et sp. nov. Holotype female. 1 — habitus dorsal; 2 — habitus, lateral; 3 — rostral area, left side; 4 — genital double somite, left side; 5 — urosome, ventral; 6 — mandibular blade; 7 — maxilliped. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208023/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number box="[858,875,367,390]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
: 
<number box="[889,902,366,390]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="1.0">1</number>
), nearly 
<number box="[1007,1042,366,390]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times as long as urosome and 
<number box="[1401,1436,366,390]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="2.2">2.2</number>
times as long as wide. The first pediger fused to cephalosome, pedigers fourth and fifth fused (
<figureCitation box="[1210,1280,402,426]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,249,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[197,1389,905,1964]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[192,1395,903,1969]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Pertsovius serratus gen. et sp. nov. Holotype female. 1 — habitus dorsal; 2 — habitus, lateral; 3 — rostral area, left side; 4 — genital double somite, left side; 5 — urosome, ventral; 6 — mandibular blade; 7 — maxilliped. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208023/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number box="[1263,1280,403,426]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
: 
<number box="[1292,1309,402,426]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,258,858]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44">
Genital double somite slightly asymmetrical, with appreciable convexity on each side; curvature on right side more pronounced (
<figureCitation box="[363,433,474,498]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,249,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[197,1389,905,1964]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[192,1395,903,1969]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Pertsovius serratus gen. et sp. nov. Holotype female. 1 — habitus dorsal; 2 — habitus, lateral; 3 — rostral area, left side; 4 — genital double somite, left side; 5 — urosome, ventral; 6 — mandibular blade; 7 — maxilliped. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208023/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number box="[416,433,475,498]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
: 
<number box="[445,461,474,498]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="5.0">5</number>
). Spermathecae visible in ventral view but difficult to see in lateral view. Anterior part of genital complex protruding strongly ventrally, forming thick wide fold, covering middle part of double somite (
<figureCitation box="[159,228,546,570]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,249,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[197,1389,905,1964]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[192,1395,903,1969]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Pertsovius serratus gen. et sp. nov. Holotype female. 1 — habitus dorsal; 2 — habitus, lateral; 3 — rostral area, left side; 4 — genital double somite, left side; 5 — urosome, ventral; 6 — mandibular blade; 7 — maxilliped. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208023/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number box="[211,228,547,570]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
: 
<number box="[240,257,546,570]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="4.0">4</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,258,858]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44">
Antennule of 
<number box="[350,378,582,606]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="24.0">24</number>
free segments and extending to proximal border of caudal rami (
<figureCitation box="[1103,1172,582,606]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,249,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[197,1389,905,1964]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[192,1395,903,1969]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Pertsovius serratus gen. et sp. nov. Holotype female. 1 — habitus dorsal; 2 — habitus, lateral; 3 — rostral area, left side; 4 — genital double somite, left side; 5 — urosome, ventral; 6 — mandibular blade; 7 — maxilliped. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208023/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number box="[1155,1172,583,606]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
: 
<number box="[1184,1201,582,606]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
). Mouthparts as in 
<taxonomicName class="Maxillopoda" family="Discoidae" genus="Pertsovius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Calanoida" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="44">P. tridentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with first lobe of maxilliped syncoxa with one seta (
<figureCitation box="[879,949,618,642]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,249,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[197,1389,905,1964]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[192,1395,903,1969]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Pertsovius serratus gen. et sp. nov. Holotype female. 1 — habitus dorsal; 2 — habitus, lateral; 3 — rostral area, left side; 4 — genital double somite, left side; 5 — urosome, ventral; 6 — mandibular blade; 7 — maxilliped. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208023/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number box="[932,949,619,642]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
: 
<number box="[961,977,618,642]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="7.0">7</number>
); no substantial differences from similar appendages of other species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,258,858]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44">
Р 
<number box="[212,224,690,714]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="1.0">1</number>
-Р 
<number box="[251,265,690,714]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="4.0">4</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[282,352,690,714]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="11.[151,249,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[214,1373,911,1920]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[204,1382,911,1931]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 8. Pertsovius serratus gen. et sp. nov. Holotype female. 1 — P 1; 2 — left Р 2; 3 — distal segment of the right exopod of Р 2; 4 — Р 3; 5 — Р 4. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208024/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number box="[335,352,690,714]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
: 
<number box="[365,407,690,714]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="3.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="1.0">1–5</number>
) of typical structure for genus: endopods one-segmented, exopods three-segmented. Outer distal spine on first segment of P 
<number box="[519,529,726,750]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="1.0">1</number>
exopod extending almost to base of outer proximal spine of third segment. Outer spine of first exopodal segment of Р 
<number box="[565,579,762,786]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
reaching beyond base of spine of second segment; both spines of identical length. Lateral borders of P 
<number box="[462,476,798,822]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
third exopod segment on left and right bearing two spines, proximal part of left segment ornamented with three small denticles (
<figureCitation box="[655,725,834,858]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="11.[151,249,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[214,1373,911,1920]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[204,1382,911,1931]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 8. Pertsovius serratus gen. et sp. nov. Holotype female. 1 — P 1; 2 — left Р 2; 3 — distal segment of the right exopod of Р 2; 4 — Р 3; 5 — Р 4. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208024/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number box="[708,725,834,858]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
: 
<number box="[736,753,834,858]" pageId="11" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
).
</paragraph>
