<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,151,284]" pageId="12" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,459,151,176]" pageId="12" pageNumber="45">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
The presence of denticles on the outer edge of the third exopodal segment of the left Р 
<number box="[1422,1436,151,175]" pageId="12" pageNumber="45" value="2.0">2</number>
and the appearance of the genital fields separate this species from other species of the genus. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,332,224,248]" pageId="12" pageNumber="45">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name reflects the presence of denticles at the external edge of the distal segment of the left P 
<number box="[252,266,260,284]" pageId="12" pageNumber="45" value="2.0">2</number>
exopod.
</paragraph>
